---
/**
 * /sms — SMS Information Service compliance page.
 *
 * Documents the opt-in SMS service for TCPA/CTIA carrier registration.
 * The AI receptionist captures verbal consent on calls; this page is
 * the public-facing service description that carriers, regulators, and
 * curious users can reference.
 *
 * Created 2026-05-13 to support SMS program approval. Content sourced
 * from ops + counsel-reviewed wording. Mirrors the legal-section
 * pattern used by /privacy /terms /accessibility:
 *   - Numbered sections with H2 headers
 *   - Glow-bordered preamble call-out
 *   - Contact block at the bottom
 *   - Italic jurisdiction line under a hairline divider
 *
 * Cross-references:
 *   - /privacy Section 3 ("SMS Messaging Program") covers the same
 *     program from the privacy-policy angle. The two pages should stay
 *     consistent; counsel review should re-confirm any divergence.
 *   - /terms covers SMS Terms and Conditions (general TOS).
 *
 * Legal note: This is the working draft for SMS messaging program
 * approval. Counsel should confirm the verbal consent script and the
 * consent-documentation language match the recorded-call evidence
 * chain we maintain.
 */
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import SnapFooter from "../components/snap/SnapFooter.astro";
import BreadcrumbSchema from "../components/BreadcrumbSchema.astro";

const LAST_UPDATED = "May 13, 2026";
---
<Base
  title="SMS Information Service | Twisted Pin"
  description="How Twisted Pin's opt-in SMS service works — verbal consent during AI receptionist calls, single informational text messages, full opt-out anytime. Plainfield, IL."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex,follow" />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="t2-hero" data-hero aria-labelledby="sms-h1">
    <div class="t2-hero-copy">
      <p class="t-eyebrow hero-fade" data-delay-ms="0">Twisted Pin</p>
      <h1 class="t-display t2-hero-headline hero-fade" id="sms-h1" data-delay-ms="120">
        SMS Information Service.
      </h1>
      <p class="t2-hero-sub hero-fade" data-delay-ms="320">
        Last updated {LAST_UPDATED}. How our opt-in SMS service works,
        what we send, and how to opt out at any time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="t2-section legal-section" aria-labelledby="sms-h2-1">
    <div class="t2-section-inner">
      <p class="legal-preamble">
        Twisted Pin ("Twisted Pin," "we," "us," "our") is a brand operated
        by Dow Holdings Inc, an Illinois corporation. We offer an opt-in
        SMS service that lets callers receive a single informational text
        message after speaking with our AI receptionist. This page
        documents the service, your consent options, and how to opt out
        at any time.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h2" id="sms-h2-1">1. Service description</h2>
      <p>
        When a caller asks our AI receptionist to text them business
        information — such as pricing, hours, directions, or location —
        we send a single transactional SMS containing a link to the
        requested information on twistedpin.com.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h2" id="sms-h2-2">2. Message frequency</h2>
      <p>
        One message per call request. Most callers receive zero or one
        messages per interaction. No recurring messages, promotional
        broadcasts, or unsolicited follow-ups.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h2" id="sms-h2-3">3. Message and data rates</h2>
      <p>
        Standard message and data rates may apply, depending on your
        mobile carrier.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h2" id="sms-h2-4">4. Verbal consent script</h2>
      <p>
        Our AI receptionist captures explicit verbal consent before
        sending any SMS. The full script:
      </p>
      <blockquote class="legal-blockquote">
        "As part of our service we can send you a single text message
        with the [pricing / hours / directions] you asked about. We'll
        send one informational message. Message and data rates may
        apply, depending on your mobile carrier. You can reply HELP for
        assistance or STOP to opt out at any time. Our Terms of Service
        are at twistedpin.com/terms and our Privacy Policy at
        twistedpin.com/privacy. Please reply with 'yes' or 'no' to
        confirm you'd like to receive this text."
      </blockquote>
      <p>
        If the caller verbally affirms, the agent confirms enrollment
        ("Great — sending it now") and the SMS is sent. If the caller
        declines, no message is sent and no further attempt is made
        during the call.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h2" id="sms-h2-5">5. Help and opt-out</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Reply <strong>HELP</strong> to any message for assistance.</li>
        <li>Reply <strong>STOP</strong> to any message to opt out at any time.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Opt-out requests are honored immediately. No further messages
        are sent to opted-out numbers.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h2" id="sms-h2-6">6. Related policies</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/terms/">SMS Terms and Conditions</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="legal-h2" id="sms-h2-7">7. Consent documentation</h2>
      <p>
        All calls to our business line are recorded. The verbal consent
        moment is logged with date, timestamp, and caller phone number.
        Recordings serve as proof of consent and are retained per our
        <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> data retention schedule.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h2" id="sms-h2-8">8. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about this SMS service or to verify your enrollment status:</p>
      <ul class="legal-contact">
        <li><strong>Business:</strong> Twisted Pin (operated by Dow Holdings Inc)</li>
        <li><strong>Address:</strong> 15610 Joliet Rd, Plainfield, IL 60544</li>
        <li><strong>Phone:</strong> 815-782-7790</li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href={`mailto:contactus@twistedpin.com?subject=${encodeURIComponent("SMS Service Question")}&body=${encodeURIComponent("Hi,\n\n")}`}>contactus@twistedpin.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <p class="legal-jurisdiction">
        Twisted Pin's SMS service operates in compliance with TCPA
        regulations and CTIA messaging guidelines.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SnapFooter />
  <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[
    { name: "Home", path: "/" },
    { name: "SMS Information", path: "/sms/" },
  ]} />
</Base>

<style>
  /* Legal pages share a vocabulary — tighter line-height, scannable
     section breaks, dim long-form copy on indigo. Same recipe as
     /privacy /terms /accessibility. Duplicated here pending a future
     hoist to a shared partial when the fourth use lands. */
  .legal-section .t2-section-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  /* Preamble paragraph — sits before Section 1, sets the legal-entity
     and scope context. Slightly heavier than body to mark its role. */
  .legal-preamble {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15.5px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--warm-mid);
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    padding: 16px 18px;
    background: rgba(244, 239, 227, 0.04);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--glow);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  }

  .legal-h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: 22px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    color: var(--warm-white);
    margin: 40px 0 14px;
  }
  .legal-h2:first-child { margin-top: 8px; }
  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .legal-h2 { font-size: 26px; margin-top: 48px; }
  }

  .legal-section p,
  .legal-section li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--warm-mid);
  }
  .legal-section p { margin: 0 0 14px; }

  .legal-section ul {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    padding-left: 22px;
  }
  .legal-section li { margin-bottom: 6px; }

  .legal-section strong { color: var(--warm-white); font-weight: 700; }

  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--glow);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* Verbal consent script — distinct treatment so it reads as the
     literal script our agent recites on calls, not commentary about
     it. Slightly brighter text + same glow border vocabulary as the
     preamble so the two compliance-critical blocks read as a pair. */
  .legal-blockquote {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--warm-white);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    padding: 18px 22px;
    background: rgba(244, 239, 227, 0.05);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--glow);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  }

  .legal-contact {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .legal-jurisdiction {
    margin-top: 32px;
    padding-top: 20px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(244, 239, 227, 0.10);
    font-size: 13px !important;
    color: var(--warm-dim) !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
